{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775847924692,"sessionID":"ses_2873ba3c4ffeb7MUp3Zh7kOMgM","part":{"id":"prt_d78c8de79001tY0KkRPkb92zXK","messageID":"msg_d78c8d0fc001VbxaVRihnYrPqP","sessionID":"ses_2873ba3c4ffeb7MUp3Zh7kOMgM","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_356e05a8450a4021b9da81d3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-008/VERIFICATION_REPORT.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-008/VERIFICATION_REPORT.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 Verification Report\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: **AR**: AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制  \n6: **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n7: **Language**: Go  \n8: **Size**: S  \n9: **Verification Date**: 2026-04-11  \n10: **Status**: ✅ **MOSTLY COMPLIANT** (with noted gaps)\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Spec Requirements vs Implementation\n15: \n16: ### 1. GC Core Implementation ✅\n17: \n18: | Spec Requirement | Implementation Status | Evidence |\n19: |-----------------|----------------------|----------|\n20: | `GarbageCollector` struct with config, client, store, context | ✅ Implemented | `garbage_collector.go:32-38` |\n21: | Constructor `NewGarbageCollector()` | ✅ Implemented | `garbage_collector.go:40-53` |\n22: | `Start()` method to run GC loop | ✅ Implemented | `garbage_collector.go:55-58` |\n23: | `Stop()` method for graceful shutdown | ✅ Implemented | `garbage_collector.go:60-63` |\n24: | `gcLoop()` with ticker-based scheduling | ✅ Implemented | `garbage_collector.go:64-78` |\n25: | `tick()` method for GC scan | ✅ Implemented | `garbage_collector.go:80-103` |\n26: \n27: **Analysis**: The GC core logic is implemented correctly with proper lifecycle management (Start/Stop), context-based cancellation, and ticker-driven periodic execution.\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ### 2. GC Policies & Configuration ⚠️\n32: \n33: | Spec Requirement | Implementation Status | Evidence |\n34: |-----------------|----------------------|----------|\n35: | Idle timeout detection | ✅ Implemented | Uses `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15m` from `defaults.go:7` |\n36: | Expired sandbox detection | ✅ Implemented | `garbage_collector.go:97-103` |\n37: | Configurable GC interval | ✅ Implemented | `GCInterval = 15s` from `defaults.go:8`, passed to constructor |\n38: | Context timeout per tick | ✅ Implemented | `GCSingleTickTimeout = 2m` from `defaults.go:9` |\n39: | Delete operation timeout | ✅ Implemented | `DeleteTimeout = 30s` from `defaults.go:10` |\n40: | **Config struct for GC** | ❌ **MISSING** | No `GCConfig` struct as specified in TASK-001 |\n41: | **MaxIdleCount enforcement** | ❌ **MISSING** | No max idle count limit implemented |\n42: | **DryRun mode** | ❌ **MISSING** | No dry-run capability |\n43: \n44: **Analysis**: Basic GC policies are implemented but the advanced configuration features from the tasks.md spec are missing (GCConfig, MaxIdleCount, DryRun).\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: ### 3. Cleanup Mechanisms ✅\n49: \n50: | Spec Requirement | Implementation Status | Evidence |\n51: |-----------------|----------------------|----------|\n52: | Delete idle sandboxes (exceeding idle timeout) | ✅ Implemented | `garbage_collector.go:86-94` |\n53: | Delete expired sandboxes | ✅ Implemented | `garbage_collector.go:97-103` |\n54: | Support both AgentRuntime and SandboxClaim kinds | ✅ Implemented | `garbage_collector.go:120-125` |\n55: | Store cleanup after K8s deletion | ✅ Implemented | `garbage_collector.go:135-138` |\n56: | NotFound tolerance | ✅ Implemented | `garbage_collector.go:132-134` |\n57: | Audit logging | ✅ Implemented | `garbage_collector.go:147-152` |\n58: \n59: **Analysis**: The cleanup mechanism correctly handles both idle and expired sandboxes, with proper error handling for NotFound cases and audit trail logging.\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ### 4. Activity Tracking ⚠️\n64: \n65: | Spec Requirement | Implementation Status | Evidence |\n66: |-----------------|----------------------|----------|\n67: | Store last activity timestamp | ✅ Implemented (in store) | Uses `LastActivityAt` field from `SandboxInfo` |\n68: | `ListInactiveSandboxes()` | ✅ Implemented | Called from store client |\n69: | `ListExpiredSandboxes()` | ✅ Implemented | Called from store client |\n70: | **Activity tracker middleware** | ❌ **MISSING** | No `LastActivityTracker` as per TASK-020 |\n71: | **Activity integration with HTTP** | ❌ **MISSING** | No middleware integration |\n72: \n73: **Analysis**: Activity tracking relies on the store interface but lacks the dedicated activity tracker and middleware integration specified in the tasks.\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ### 5. Metrics ⚠️\n78: \n79: | Spec Requirement | Implementation Status | Evidence |\n80: |-----------------|----------------------|----------|\n81: | **Prometheus metrics (gcRuns, gcDuration, etc.)** | ❌ **MISSING** | No metrics implementation |\n82: | **GCMetrics struct** | ❌ **MISSING** | No metrics struct |\n83: | **State counting** | ❌ **MISSING** | No state-based gauges |\n84: \n85: **Analysis**: No metrics are currently exported. This is a significant gap for production monitoring.\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: ### 6. State Management ⚠️\n90: \n91: | Spec Requirement | Implementation Status | Evidence |\n92: |-----------------|----------------------|----------|\n93: | **SandboxState enum (Active, Idle, Orphaned, Expired)** | ❌ **MISSING** | No state enum defined |\n94: | **GCCandidate struct** | ❌ **MISSING** | Uses `SandboxInfo` directly |\n95: | **evaluateState() method** | ❌ **MISSING** | State evaluation is implicit in store queries |\n96: \n97: **Analysis**: The implementation takes a simpler approach by delegating state evaluation to the store layer rather than implementing explicit state machine logic.\n98: \n99: ---\n100: \n101: ### 7. Testing ✅\n102: \n103: | Test | Status | Location |\n104: |------|--------|----------|\n105: | `TestNewGarbageCollector` | ✅ PASS | `garbage_collector_test.go:61-86` |\n106: | `TestGarbageCollector_StartStop` | ✅ PASS | `garbage_collector_test.go:88-99` |\n107: | `TestGarbageCollector_Tick_IdleCleanup` | ✅ PASS | `garbage_collector_test.go:101-122` |\n108: | `TestGarbageCollector_Tick_ExpiredCleanup` | ✅ PASS | `garbage_collector_test.go:124-147` |\n109: | `TestGarbageCollector_DeleteSandbox_NotFound` | ✅ PASS | `garbage_collector_test.go:149-168` |\n110: | `TestGarbageCollector_DeleteSandbox_StoreError` | ✅ PASS | `garbage_collector_test.go:170-189` |\n111: | `TestGarbageCollector_Tick_ContextTimeout` | ✅ PASS | `garbage_collector_test.go:191-210` |\n112: | `TestGarbageCollector_Tick_StoreError` | ✅ PASS | `garbage_collector_test.go:212-224` |\n113: \n114: **Test Coverage**: 8 passing tests covering construction, lifecycle, idle cleanup, expired cleanup, error handling, and timeout scenarios.\n115: \n116: **Missing Tests** (per tasks.md):\n117: - ❌ Activity tracker tests (TASK-020 to TASK-023)\n118: - ❌ Metrics tests (TASK-030 to TASK-032)\n119: - ❌ Integration tests (TEST-050, TEST-051)\n120: - ❠ MaxIdleCount tests (depends on missing feature)\n121: - ❠ DryRun tests (depends on missing feature)\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ### 8. client-go Library Verification ⚠️\n126: \n127: The spec references a generated `client-go` library at `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`. **This directory does not exist** in the current workspace.\n128: \n129: | Spec Component | Status |\n130: |---------------|--------|\n131: | `clientset/versioned/clientset.go` | ❌ Not found |\n132: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go` | ❌ Not found |\n133: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | ❌ Not found |\n134: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | ❌ Not found |\n135: | `informers/externalversions/factory.go` | ❌ Not found |\n136: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/` | ❌ Not found |\n137: | Fake clients | ❌ Not found |\n138: \n139: **Analysis**: The client-go library has not been generated yet. The GC implementation uses `dynamic.Interface` instead of the typed client, which works but doesn't match the spec's architecture.\n140: \n141: ---\n142: \n143: ### 9. Configuration Integration ❌\n144: \n145: | Spec Requirement | Status |\n146: |-----------------|--------|\n147: | GC flags in `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` | ❌ Missing (no cmd directory found) |\n148: | Environment variables (`GC_ENABLED`, `GC_INTERVAL`, etc.) | ❌ Not documented or used |\n149: | Integration with main startup | ❌ Not visible |\n150: \n151: **Analysis**: No integration with the main entry point is visible. The GC can be constructed but there's no evidence of it being wired into the application startup.\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ### 10. Documentation ⚠️\n156: \n157: | Requirement | Status |\n158: |------------|--------|\n159: | Package documentation (`doc.go`) | ❌ Missing |\n160: | Godoc comments on public types | ⚠️ Partial (some comments present) |\n161: | README update | ❌ Not in `changes/AR-008/` |\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ## Gaps Summary\n166: \n167: ### Critical Gaps (P0)\n168: 1. **client-go library not generated** - The spec assumes a typed client that doesn't exist\n169: 2. **No main integration** - GC is not wired into application startup\n170: 3. **No metrics** - Production monitoring capability missing\n171: \n172: ### High Priority Gaps (P1)\n173: 4. **Missing GCConfig** - Configuration is hardcoded rather than configurable\n174: 5. **No MaxIdleCount enforcement** - Cannot limit number of idle sandboxes\n175: 6. **No DryRun mode** - Cannot test GC without actual deletion\n176: 7. **No activity tracker middleware** - Activity tracking is passive\n177: \n178: ### Medium Priority Gaps (P2)\n179: 8. **Missing state machine** - No explicit SandboxState enum or evaluation\n180: 9. **Incomplete documentation** - Missing package docs and godoc comments\n181: 10. **No integration tests** - Only unit tests present\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ## Test Results Summary\n186: \n187: ```\n188: Package: github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager\n189: GC Tests: 8/8 PASS\n190: Coverage: ~43% (module-wide, includes non-GC code)\n191: ```\n192: \n193: **Passing Tests**:\n194: - ✅ TestNewGarbageCollector\n195: - ✅ TestGarbageCollector_StartStop\n196: - ✅ TestGarbageCollector_Tick_IdleCleanup\n197: - ✅ TestGarbageCollector_Tick_ExpiredCleanup\n198: - ✅ TestGarbageCollector_DeleteSandbox_NotFound\n199: - ✅ TestGarbageCollector_DeleteSandbox_StoreError\n200: - ✅ TestGarbageCollector_Tick_ContextTimeout\n201: - ✅ TestGarbageCollector_Tick_StoreError\n202: \n203: **Failing Tests** (in related packages):\n204: - ❌ TestBuildSandboxObject (processor package - unrelated to GC)\n205: - ❌ TestBuildCodeInterpreterSandbox (processor package - unrelated to GC)\n206: - ❌ reconciler package build failure (missing json import)\n207: \n208: ---\n209: \n210: ## Compliance Matrix\n211: \n212: | Category | Requirements Met | Total | Compliance |\n213: |----------|-----------------|-------|------------|\n214: | Core GC Logic | 6/6 | 6 | 100% ✅ |\n215: | GC Policies | 5/8 | 8 | 62% ⚠️ |\n216: | Cleanup Mechanisms | 6/6 | 6 | 100% ✅ |\n217: | Activity Tracking | 2/4 | 4 | 50% ⚠️ |\n218: | Metrics | 0/4 | 4 | 0% ❌ |\n219: | State Management | 0/3 | 3 | 0% ❌ |\n220: | Testing | 8/13 | 13 | 62% ⚠️ |\n221: | client-go Library | 0/7 | 7 | 0% ❌ |\n222: | Configuration | 0/3 | 3 | 0% ❌ |\n223: | Documentation | 1/3 | 3 | 33% ❌ |\n224: | **OVERALL** | **28/57** | **57** | **49%** ⚠️ |\n225: \n226: ---\n227: \n228: ## Recommendations\n229: \n230: ### Immediate Actions (Required for Spec Compliance)\n231: 1. **Generate client-go library**: Run `make gen-client` to generate typed clients\n232: 2. **Wire GC into main**: Integrate GC startup/shutdown with application lifecycle\n233: 3. **Add GCConfig**: Create configuration struct with flags/env vars\n234: \n235: ### Short-term Improvements\n236: 4. **Implement metrics**: Add Prometheus metrics for GC operations\n237: 5. **Add MaxIdleCount**: Implement idle sandbox count limiting\n238: 6. **Add DryRun mode**: Enable safe testing of GC policies\n239: \n240: ### Long-term Enhancements\n241: 7. **State machine**: Explicit state tracking and evaluation\n242: 8. **Activity middleware**: HTTP middleware for activity tracking\n243: 9. **Integration tests**: End-to-end tests with real Kubernetes\n244: 10. **Documentation**: Complete godoc and user documentation\n245: \n246: ---\n247: \n248: ## Conclusion\n249: \n250: The AR-008 implementation provides a **functional but incomplete** sandbox garbage collection mechanism. The core GC logic is solid with proper lifecycle management, idle/expired sandbox detection, and comprehensive unit tests. However, significant gaps exist in:\n251: \n252: - Generated client-go library (completely missing)\n253: - Application integration (not wired into main)\n254: - Advanced features (metrics, config, dry-run, max idle count)\n255: - Documentation\n256: \n257: **Verdict**: The implementation satisfies the **minimum viable product** for GC functionality but does not fully comply with the detailed specification in `tasks.md`. Priority should be given to generating the client-go library, integrating GC into the application, and adding metrics for production readiness.\n258: \n259: ---\n260: \n261: ## Appendix: File Locations\n262: \n263: ### Implemented Files\n264: - `/pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` - Core GC implementation\n265: - `/pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go` - Unit tests\n266: - `/pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` - GC constants\n267: - `/pkg/workloadmanager/types/sandbox_types.go` - Sandbox data structures\n268: \n269: ### Missing Files (per spec)\n270: - `/client-go/` - Generated client library\n271: - `/pkg/workloadmanager/gc/config.go` - GC configuration\n272: - `/pkg/workloadmanager/gc/state.go` - State definitions\n273: - `/pkg/workloadmanager/gc/candidate.go` - GCCandidate type\n274: - `/pkg/workloadmanager/gc/activity.go` - Activity tracker\n275: - `/pkg/workloadmanager/gc/metrics.go` - Metrics implementation\n276: - `/cmd/workload-manager/main.go` - Application entry point\n\n(End of file - total 276 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 Verification Report\n\n## Summary\n\n**AR**: AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制  \n**Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language**: Go  \n**Size**: S  \n**Verification Date**: 2026-04-11  \n**Status**: ✅ **MOSTLY COMPLIANT** (with noted gaps)\n\n---\n\n## Spec Requirements vs Implementation\n\n### 1. GC Core Implementation ✅\n\n| Spec Requirement | Implementation Status | Evidence |\n|-----------------|----------------------|----------|\n| `GarbageCollector` struct with config, client, store, context | ✅ Implemented | `garbage_collector.go:32-38` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-008/VERIFICATION_REPORT.md","time":{"start":1775847924681,"end":1775847924690}}}}
